    <h2>Summary:</h2>
    <p>
      We were interested in learning more about the architecture of the American prison system.
      After finding a JSON file with a plethora of data on Kaggle, we have created this page to display a visual representation of that data.
      Statistics such as how many crimes are committed, what types of crimes are committed, and how many prisoners there are, all give insight
      into how crime is viewed and regulated in a given state. We created a webpage that allows you to view a wide variety of crime metrics across the entire nation
      as well as in specific states in order to make information about the crime distribution across the nation more readable and accessible.
    </p>

    <h2>Comparison:</h2>
    <p>
      The United States has a total population of 3500000000 people. From 2001-2016, the total crime (property crime and violent crime) amounted to 13173233.
      The United States has a crime per capita metric of 20317 crimes per 100,000 people.
      The United States crime per capita is BELOW AVERAGE with the US crime per capita being X.
      The number of crimes committed in NY is x% of the US total crime (property and violent crime total)
    </p>

